xbrlcore.xlink
Class Arc

java.lang.Object
  xbrlcore.xlink.Arc
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable
public class Arc
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable

This class represents an arc in a linkbase file. Its most important attributes are a source and a target element as well as an arcrole indicating the semantic meaning of the arc.

Author:
Daniel Hamm

Method Detail

equals

public boolean equals(java.lang.Object obj)
Checks if two Arc objects are equal. This is true if and only if:
- both have the same source element
- both have the same target element
- both are within the same extended link role
- both have the same value in their "use" attribute
- both have the same value in their "priority" attribute
-the non-XLink attributes of both are s-equal

Overrides:
equals in class java.lang.Object
Parameters:
obj - The object the current Arc is checked against.
Returns:
True if both Arc objects are equal, false otherwise.

equalSource

public boolean equalSource(java.lang.Object obj)
Checks if two Arc objects have the same source. This is true if and only if:
- the source locators of both arcs refer to the same concept
- both arcs are in the same extended link role

Parameters:
obj - The object the current Arc is checked against.
Returns:

hasSameAttributes

public boolean hasSameAttributes(Arc arcToCompare)
Checks whether two arcs have s-equal non-XLink attributes (except "use" and "priority"), which is one requirement to be of equivalent relationship as described in Spec. chapter 3.5.3.9.7.4.

Parameters:
arcToCompare - Arc which attributes are compared to the attributes of this arc.
Returns:
True if the value of any non-XLink attribute except "use" and "priority" is s-equal to the same non-XLink attribute on the other arc.
